definition: to set up/to arrange/to establish/to found/to display

sentences.english: An existing replicate can be redefined by remastering the replicate.
sentences.chinese: 通过重设主控可以重新定义现有的复制。

sentences.english: This is the best way to reset your sleep schedule.
sentences.chinese: 这是最好的重设你睡眠时间表的方法。

sentences.english: If it is too long, reset action will be very slow to take effect.
sentences.chinese: 如果设置过长，重设动作将会非常慢。

sentences.english: When resized, a metafile preserves an image better than a bitmap.
sentences.chinese: 重设大小时，中继档保存的影像优于点阵图。

sentences.english: Resetting to factory defaults will restore remote Non-Volatile user settings.
sentences.chinese: 重设为工厂默认值会恢复远程非易失用户设置。

sentences.english: Under my leadership, my department realigned the way we source and market projects.
sentences.chinese: 在我的领导下，我们重设了资源和市场计划。

sentences.english: Overriding the default mapping registry with the new type mappings.
sentences.chinese: 用新的类型映射重设缺省的映射注册表。

sentences.english: And huge waves of mortgage resets are due over the next two years.
sentences.chinese: 未来两年还有巨额的重设过的抵押贷款将到期。

sentences.english: I have to reset your converter boxes.
sentences.chinese: 我必须得重设你的转换盒。

sentences.english: Remastering allows you to change what columns are in a replicate definition without interrupting the replication.
sentences.chinese: 重设主控允许改变复制定义中的列，而不用中止复制。

sentences.english: Each setting will be restored to its default value.
sentences.chinese: 每个设置指标将被重设到其初始数值。

sentences.english: An option to reset the password will display.
They slip out as Tuxhorn resets his alarm.
sentences.chinese: 在塔克斯宏重设报警器之前溜了出来。

sentences.english: Whether the image collection pane should be resizable or not.
sentences.chinese: 图片集窗格是否可以重设大小。

sentences.english: Of course you don't have to reset your loss-limit after every single pot or even at all.
sentences.chinese: 当然，没有必要再每一轮之后都重设损失上限。

sentences.english: Resize the icons, using that new slider in the status bar.
sentences.chinese: 用状态栏的新滑块重设图标的大小。

definition: to unbind (e.g. a phone number from an account)
